      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NEVERENOUGHLEGO (5) brought strong form from a top Victorian stable and belted the Maidens here by 4.5L off a 58-day freshen. A senior hoop replaces the apprentice, and he has more to give. Nicely placed to double the win tally. TEN CARAT LUCY (6) peaks off three narrow defeats at the track, and she was heavily bet over 1200m the latest. Maps well, and the 2kg claim is handy. Comes back to the shorter sprint, and she should be right in it again. BLITZWATER (3) resumes and raced in a rich Quality at the Sunshine Coast when last seen on race day. Went close over 1200m at the Gold Coast in a 58 as a $2.6F, the one before, and owns a recent trial placing. Draws low and a bold return is likely. MARELLITY (7) was a bit plainer over this trip at Mackay, but her form prior was pretty solid. Tumbles in weight this grade with a 3kg claim atop, and that brings her into it.",
